# TypeScript Standards

## Error Handling

```typescript
// ❌ BAD
try {
  await fetchData();
} catch (e) {}

// ✅ GOOD
try {
  await fetchData();
} catch (e) {
  console.error('Failed to fetch', e);
  throw new Error('Unable to retrieve data', { cause: e });
}
```

## Types
- Prefer `interface` for object shapes
- Avoid `any`; use `unknown` when type is unclear, then narrow
- Export types that are used across modules
